                    <h1>Privacy Policy for Auroras Best Bricks</h1>
                    <p>This Privacy Policy outlines how Auroras Best Bricks ("we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, maintains, and discloses information gathered from users (each, a "User") of the www.AurorasBestBricks.com website ("Site"). This privacy policy applies to the Site and all products and services offered by Auroras Best Bricks.</p>

                    <h2>Data Controller</h2>
                    <p>Auroras Best Bricks acts as a Data Controller as defined under the GDPR. We process personal data primarily to enable Users to place orders and engage with our services. All personal data collected by Auroras Best Bricks is stored securely within data centers located in the European Economic Area (EEA).</p>

                    <h2>Collection of Personal Identification Information</h2>
                    <p>We collect personal identification information in several ways, including when Users visit our Site, register, or place an order. We may ask for, as appropriate, your name, email address, postal address, phone number, and Tax ID. Users can visit our Site anonymously but providing personal identification information is voluntary. However, refusal to supply such information may prevent Users from engaging in certain Site-related activities.</p>

                    <h2>Non-Personal Identification Information</h2>
                    <p>Non-personal identification information about Users may be collected whenever they interact with our Site. This may include the browser name, the type of computer, and technical information about Users' means of connection to our Site, such as the operating system, the Internet service providers utilized, and other similar information.</p>

                    <h2>Cookies</h2>
                    <p>Our Site uses "cookies" to enhance the User experience. Users' web browsers place cookies on their hard drives for record-keeping purposes and sometimes to track information about them. Users can set their web browser to refuse cookies or to alert them when cookies are being sent. If they do so, some parts of the Site may not function properly.</p>

                    <h2>Usage of Collected Information</h2>
                    <p>Auroras Best Bricks may use the collected personal information for the following purposes:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>To improve customer service</li>
                        <li>To personalize user experience</li>
                        <li>To enhance our Site</li>
                        <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
                        <li>To process transactions</li>
                        <li>To run promotions, contests, or surveys</li>
                        <li>To send periodic emails regarding the Site or user orders</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>User Rights and Access to Information</h2>
                    <p>Users have the right under GDPR to access personal information we hold about them. Requests for access, correction, or deletion can be made through the user profile or by contacting us directly.</p>

                    <h2>Protection of Your Information</h2>
                    <p>We adopt appropriate data collection, storage, processing, and security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of personal information.</p>

                    <h2>Sharing of Personal Information</h2>
                    <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent Users' personal identification information. We may share information with third parties only in ways that are described in this privacy policy and in compliance with GDPR requirements.</p>

                    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
                    <p>We retain Personal Data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected or as required by law.</p>

                    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
                    <p>We reserve the right to update this privacy policy. Changes will be indicated by an updated date at the bottom of the page.</p>

